
[1]successor

   SUCCESS'OR, n. [L.] One that succeeds or follows; one that takes the
   place which another has left, and sustains the like part or character;
   correlative to predecessor; as the successor of a deceased king; the
   successor of a president or governor; a man's son and successor.

   A gift to a corporation, either of lands or of chattels, without naming
   their successors,vests an absolute property in them so long as the
   corporation subsists.
